                <div class="over">
                    <h4>Day 1: Bowling Action<br>and Alignment</h4>
                    <p>
                        <li>Balance Drill: Focus on your balance during the run-up and delivery stride. Bowl while balancing on one leg to improve your stability and control.</li>
                        <li>Cones Drill: Set up cones at a good length on the pitch and target them consistently. Work on hitting the same spot repeatedly to improve line and length accuracy.</li>
                        <li>Wrist Position Drill: Use a partner or coach to observe and correct your wrist position during delivery. Maintain a strong seam position for seam movement and swing..</li>
                       
                    
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card" id="card2">
                <div class="over">
                    <h4>Day 2: Seam and Swing<br>Bowling</h4>
                    <p>
                        <li>Towel Drill: Place a small towel on the pitch and try to bowl with the seam pointing directly at the towel. This helps you practice seam movement and control.</li>
                        <li>Swing Bowling Drill: Use an old ball and work on swinging it both ways. Focus on your wrist position and seam orientation for conventional and reverse swing.</li>
                        <li>Variations Drill: Practice bowling slower balls, leg-cutters, and off-cutters to deceive batsmen. Work on disguising these deliveries effectively.</li>
                       
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card" id="card3">
                <div class="over">
                    <h4>Day 3: Pace and Bounce</h4>
                    <p>
                        <li>Speed Gun Drill: Use a speed gun to measure your bowling speed. Try to consistently increase your pace by working on your run-up and action.</li>
                        <li>Bounce Target Drill: Place a target on the pitch, such as a cone, and aim to hit it consistently with short-pitched deliveries. Focus on generating bounce and pace.</li>
                        
                    </p><br>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="cards-container">
            <div class="card" id="card4">
                <div class="over">
                    <h4>Day 4: Bowling Under<br>Pressure</h4>
                    <p>
                        <li>Pressure Simulation Drill: Create pressure scenarios in the nets where you have specific targets or field placements to bowl to. Simulate match-like situations to improve your ability to handle pressure.</li>
                        <li>Yorker and Slower Ball Drill: Work on your yorker delivery and practice variations of slower balls under pressure conditions.</li>
                       
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card" id="card5">
                <div class="over">
                    <h4>Day 5: Strength and<br>Conditioning</h4>
                    <p>
                        <li>Medicine Ball Exercises: Incorporate medicine ball exercises, such as overhead throws and twists, to strengthen your core and improve your bowling action's power.</li>
                        <li>Agility Ladder Drill: Use an agility ladder to work on your footwork and agility, which are essential for fast bowlers.</li>
                        
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card" id="card6">
                <div class="over">
                    <h4>Day 6: Mental Toughness<br>and Visualization</h4>
                    <p>
                        <li>Mental Toughness Visualization: Spend time visualizing different match scenarios and visualize yourself executing your skills under pressure.</li>
                        <li>Scenario-based Bowling Drills: Simulate different game situations, like bowling in the opening spell, defending a low total, or chasing a target, during your practice sessions..</li>
                        
                    </p>
                </div>
